        <h2>5-11-18: NEW WEBSITE!!! NEW SINGLE RELEASE!!!</h2>
        
        <p>We're 5 months into 2018, and I've given you silence (no pun intended). Of course this is unintentional. For those of you
          keeping tabs on my whereabouts, I've been taking a break from writing music for HFM, and have been focusing my attention
          on learning web development. Perhaps you're wondering why on earth I'd want to do such a thing... Well, the fact of the
          matter is that I'm taking a break from touring for the unforseeable future. With the reality of being at home, I felt that
          now is the time to learn something new, and to see how I can impliment this new skill into my world.
        </p>
        <p>
          The first thing I wanted to do was re-vamp my website. So, here we are. Welcome, and thank you for tuning in. The new hefailsme.com
          has been brought to you by The Crunchy Harps Group, consisting of myself, Marcus Badillo, Donovan Hedrich, and John Chambers.
          To celebrate having a new site, we've also teamed up on the music end, and we would to present you with the new single,
          "Code Break".
        </p>
        <p>
          I am not a highly political person, nor do I have an agenda to use politics to fuel my music. However, I am a compassionate
          human being, and I am a person that comes from an immigrant family. I am also a person who values the idea that the children
          are our future. I believe in human rights, racial equality, and gender equality. I am sickened by violence. I, along with
          millions of other people, have been emotionally shook on so many levels by the tragedies that have plagued not only my
          country, but worldwide. "Code Break" is a song about love. It's about how love should be taken more seriously, not just
          on a relationship standpoint, but on a global and human level. Unfortunately, I don't think love is on everyones agendas,
          especially at the highest level of our government.
        </p>
